  "title": "Restaurant Manager",
  "description": "<p>Restaurant Manager</p><p>Work Location</p><p>📍 Holland Village Station (CC21 – Circle Line / Orange Line)</p><p>Eligibility Requirements</p><p>•\tStatus: Singaporean / PR only</p><p> Experience: Minimum relevant experience in F&B / catering industry (restaurant management preferred)</p><p>Salary & Benefits</p><p>•\tBase Salary: $4,500 – $6,000+ (based on performance)</p><p>•\tMeals: 2 meals provided daily</p><p>•\tMonthly rest days: 4 days</p><p>•\tSick Leave: As per MOM regulations (3-year benefits same as MOM)</p><p>Working Hours</p><p>⏰ 10:30am – 11:00pm</p><p>✔ 2-hour break in between</p><p>Interview Method</p><p>🎥 Video interview / Face-to-face interview</p><p>⸻</p><p>Job Responsibilities</p><p>•\tAssist in daily restaurant operations management and handle emergencies</p><p>•\tEnsure restaurant meets/exceeds standards of food quality, safety, hygiene, cleanliness</p><p>•\tConduct staff training, coaching, and monitor staff performance</p><p>•\tEnforce discipline and ensure all staff comply with workplace behavior standards</p><p>•\tMaintain high morale and positive team culture in the outlet</p><p>•\tResponsible for monthly inventory checks and replenishment planning</p><p>•\tEnsure all licenses, hygiene, safety, health, sanitation standards comply with laws/regulations</p><p>•\tPrepare monthly performance reports</p><p>•\tParticipate in shift planning and manpower scheduling</p><p>⸻</p><p>Job Requirements / Candidate Profile</p><p>•\tExperience in a similar management role in the F&B / catering industry</p><p>•\tStrong leadership and people management skills</p><p>•\tExcellent communication and coordination ability</p><p>•\tProactive, capable, responsible, and able to work under pressure</p><p>•\tTeam-oriented with a positive working attitude</p>",
